CAN GRANT CLEMENCY

18:41.421 --> 18:43.290
IF THE PAROLE BOARD
RECOMMENDS IT.

18:43.290 --> 18:44.624
DID MR. AMIRI
EVER TELL YOU THAT?

18:44.624 --> 18:47.694
- I TALKED TO HIM SO LONG AGO,
I DON'T RECALL.

18:47.694 --> 18:49.496
I'D LIKE TO TALK
TO THE GOVERNOR,

18:49.496 --> 18:50.930
IF THAT'S POSSIBLE.

18:50.930 --> 18:53.900
- IT WOULD BE MORE LIKE
MR. ELLIS WOULD SPEAK FOR YOU

18:53.900 --> 18:56.569
TO THE PAROLE BOARD.

18:56.569 --> 18:58.538
- ABOUT WHAT?
- REGGIE, YOU MURDERED A MAN.

18:58.538 --> 19:00.907
AND YOU MAY NEVER
GET OUT OF PRISON.

19:00.907 --> 19:02.909
BUT IF SOMETHING
HAPPENED TO YOU,

19:02.909 --> 19:05.378
SOMETHING BAD
WHEN YOU WERE A KID,

19:05.378 --> 19:08.248
THE JURY SHOULD
HAVE HEARD ABOUT IT.

19:08.248 --> 19:12.252
- REGGIE,
BEFORE THE TRIAL,

19:12.252 --> 19:15.922
DID ANYBODY EVER ASK YOU
ABOUT YOUR CHILDHOOD?

19:15.922 --> 19:18.458
ANYBODY EVER ASK YOU
ABOUT THAT CAMP?

19:18.458 --> 19:20.393
- I MET THE LAWYER
A DAY BEFORE.

19:20.393 --> 19:22.362
WE DIDN'T TALK MUCH
ABOUT ANYTHING.

19:22.362 --> 19:25.765
- THERE'S STILL TIME.
THAT'S WHY WE'RE HERE.

19:25.765 --> 19:29.602
WE CAN TALK ABOUT IT NOW,
OKAY?

19:31.404 --> 19:33.540
REGGIE,
WE NEED YOU TO TELL US

19:33.540 --> 19:36.709
WHAT HAPPENED
AT MARTIN'S CAMP.

19:36.709 --> 19:38.578
- THE SOCIAL WORKER IN THE GROUP
USED TO ALWAYS TRY

19:38.578 --> 19:41.348
TO GET ME
TO TALK ABOUT IT.

19:41.348 --> 19:43.616
- I KNOW IT'S DIFFICULT,
REGGIE.

19:43.616 --> 19:46.453
BUT THE PAROLE BOARD HAS
TO KNOW WHAT HAPPENED TO YOU.

19:46.453 --> 19:51.491
- IT'S TOO LATE.
I'M LETTING IT GO.

19:51.491 --> 19:52.792
I FORGIVE EVERYONE
FOR EVERYTHING.

19:52.792 --> 19:54.661
I EVEN FORGIVE MY MAMA.

19:54.661 --> 19:57.297
- FORGIVE HER FOR WHAT?

19:57.297 --> 20:01.368
- FOR SENDING ME BACK
TO MARTIN'S CAMP.

20:05.338 --> 20:06.806
- DOES HE HAVE A CHANCE?
[buzzer]

20:06.806 --> 20:08.575
- AFTER THE DEFENSE HE HAD,

20:08.575 --> 20:11.411
